{"parse":{"title":"bum bag","pageid":85307,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|bumbag}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n[[File:Red Fanny Pack.jpg|right|thumb|175px|Woman wearing a bum bag]]\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{l|en|bumbag}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|en|EN-AU ck1 bum bag.ogg|a=AU}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|UK|Ireland|Commonwealth}} A small pouch attached to a belt that is worn on the outside of clothing around the waist and used for holding small personal items.\n#: {{syn|en|belt bag|fanny pack|q2=US, Canada|belly bag|q3=US|moon bag|q4=South Africa|waist bag|crossbody bag}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1995|author=Vitali Vitaliev|title=Little is the Light: Nostalgic Travels in the Mini-States of Europe|page=226|url=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=VzIdiHDtByUC&q=%22bum+bag%22%7C%22bum+bags%22+-intitle:%22bum%7Cbums%22+-inauthor:%22%22&dq=%22bum+bag%22%7C%22bum+bags%22+-intitle:%22bum%7Cbums%22+-inauthor:%22%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=f-ETT8HkL46NmQWY2rjfAw&redir_esc=y|passage=There is no queue at Burger King in Gibraltar. To lure customers, they give you a free plastic '''bum bag''' with every Whopper Meal.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2003|author=Lesley Reader; Lucy Ridout|title=First-Time Asia|pageurl=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=E12eoIKbM1cC&pg=PA230&dq=%22bum+bag%22%7C%22bum+bags%22+-intitle:%22bum%7Cbums%22+-inauthor:%22%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=f-ETT8HkL46NmQWY2rjfAw&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22bum%20bag%22%7C%22bum%20bags%22%20-intitle%3A%22bum%7Cbums%22%20-inauthor%3A%22%22&f=false|page=230\n|passage=Don′t confuse money belts with '''bum bags'''. A '''bum bag''' is a larger and an altogether more ostentatious item; it′s worn over your clothes and can usually hold a small camera as well as sunscreen and sunglasses. As a security item the '''bum bag''' is useless and may as well be inscribed with flashing lights announcing “Valuable items inside, help yourself”.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2007|author=Poul Anderson|title=Shocking Australian True Crime Stories|pageurl=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=WwHFJtJ6eREC&pg=PT55&dq=%22bum+bag%22%7C%22bum+bags%22+-intitle:%22bum%7Cbums%22+-inauthor:%22%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=f-ETT8HkL46NmQWY2rjfAw&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22bum%20bag%22%7C%22bum%20bags%22%20-intitle%3A%22bum%7Cbums%22%20-inauthor%3A%22%22&f=false|page=unnumbered\n|passage=''Berichon'': I proceeded to pull the pistol out of the '''bum bag'''. I flicked the safety switch off the pistol and I fired upon the police officer.}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-see|small pouch attached to a belt|fanny pack}}\n\n{{C|en|Bags}}"}}